  "text": "Another advantage of using ASO is that bidirectional modulation is possible for a single target, as shown here with the H2AFY G4. Interestingly, H2AFY protein isoform 1 is considered a clinically relevant cancer biomarker, including for monitoring of colorectal [CITATION_1] , hepatic [CITATION_2] and lung [CITATION_3] cancers. Importantly, the levels of this protein correlate with survival prognoses and progression of metastases. The mechanism by which H2AFY affects cancer development is, however, still poorly understood. Therefore, ASO-mediated modulation of cancer biomarkers, such as H2AFY protein expression, is one more tool that will help move research forward and contribute further insights into their roles and, possibly, provides new clinically relevant therapeutic targets.",
